column5: Got a bit earlier start this morning.Got fishing at 8 am and was into a walleye frenzy till noon.Norhing huge today all eater sized but a lot of fun hauling one after the other up plus 7 pike one with another jig.Used a lot lures today and they all worked like a charm.Much better weather now but had couple of whiteouts.Wind was howling pretty good and shook the shack a few times.
When I was up there in March a few years back nothing shook the schack at all,only when I hit my head on the door frame there were some loud jarring cuse words.
Quick vid from ice shack.Pulked about 60 of these up yesterday.https://youtu.be/JiUkVh7ECGs
Eck just thought I would show you the pic of the door in question.Fished in there other day.I did remember to duck.
Yup that's the s.o.b that just about knocked me out!!
